#. <section class="sutta" id="mn24"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "mn24:0.1"
msgid "Majjhima Nikāya 24"
msgstr "Middle Discourses 24"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "mn24:0.2"
msgid "Rathavinītasutta"
msgstr "Prepared Chariots"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya1"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "mn24:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—​"
msgstr "So I have heard."

msgctxt "mn24:1.2"
msgid "ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā rājagahe viharati veḷuvane kalandakanivāpe."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying near Rājagaha, in the Bamboo Grove, the "
"squirrels’ feeding ground."

# Comm says jatibhumi means the Buddha’s native district. I don’t think so. The word occurs at AN 6.54, Pvr 14, Ja 537, and Ja 546, and nowhere does it have any other sense than the expected “ones’ native district”.
#. <a class="nya" id="nya2"></a>
msgctxt "mn24:2.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho sambahulā jātibhūmakā bhikkhū jātibhūmiyaṃ vassaṃvuṭṭhā yena "
"bhagavā tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ "
"nisīdiṃsu. Ekamantaṃ nisinne kho te bhikkhū bhagavā etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"Then several mendicants who had completed the rainy season residence in "
"their native land went to the Buddha, bowed, and sat down to one side. The "
"Buddha said to them:"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi1.146"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "mn24:2.2"
msgid ""
"“Ko nu kho, bhikkhave, jātibhūmiyaṃ jātibhūmakānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ "
"sabrahmacārīnaṃ evaṃ sambhāvito:"
msgstr ""
"“In your native land, mendicants, which of the native mendicants is esteemed "
"in this way:"

msgctxt "mn24:2.3"
msgid ""
"‘attanā ca appiccho appicchakathañca bhikkhūnaṃ kattā, attanā ca santuṭṭho "
"santuṭṭhikathañca bhikkhūnaṃ kattā, attanā ca pavivitto pavivekakathañca "
"bhikkhūnaṃ kattā, attanā ca asaṃsaṭṭho asaṃsaggakathañca bhikkhūnaṃ kattā, "
"attanā ca āraddhavīriyo vīriyārambhakathañca bhikkhūnaṃ kattā, attanā ca "
"sīlasampanno sīlasampadākathañca bhikkhūnaṃ kattā, attanā ca samādhisampanno "
"samādhisampadākathañca bhikkhūnaṃ kattā, attanā ca paññāsampanno "
"paññāsampadākathañca bhikkhūnaṃ kattā, attanā ca vimuttisampanno "
"vimuttisampadākathañca bhikkhūnaṃ kattā, attanā ca "
"vimuttiñāṇadassanasampanno vimuttiñāṇadassanasampadākathañca bhikkhūnaṃ "
"kattā, ovādako viññāpako sandassako samādapako samuttejako sampahaṃsako "
"sabrahmacārīnan’”ti?"
msgstr ""
"‘Personally having few wishes, they speak to the mendicants on having few "
"wishes. Personally having contentment, seclusion, aloofness, energy, ethics, "
"immersion, wisdom, freedom, and the knowledge and vision of freedom, they "
"speak to the mendicants on all these things. They’re an adviser and "
"instructor, one who educates, encourages, fires up, and inspires their "
"spiritual companions.’”"

# Does this mean “son of the lady who recited the Vedas”?
msgctxt "mn24:2.4"
msgid ""
"“Puṇṇo nāma, bhante, āyasmā mantāṇiputto jātibhūmiyaṃ jātibhūmakānaṃ "
"bhikkhūnaṃ sabrahmacārīnaṃ evaṃ sambhāvito:"
msgstr "“Puṇṇa Mantāṇiputta, sir, is esteemed in this way in our native land.”"

msgctxt "mn24:2.5"
msgid ""
"‘attanā ca appiccho appicchakathañca bhikkhūnaṃ kattā, attanā ca santuṭṭho … "
"pe … ovādako viññāpako sandassako samādapako samuttejako sampahaṃsako "
"sabrahmacārīnan’”ti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya3"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "mn24:3.1"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena āyasmā sāriputto bhagavato avidūre nisinno hoti."
msgstr ""
"Now at that time Venerable Sāriputta was meditating not far from the Buddha."

msgctxt "mn24:3.2"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmato sāriputtassa etadahosi:"
msgstr "Then he thought:"

# Last phrase omitted by BB.
msgctxt "mn24:3.3"
msgid ""
"“lābhā āyasmato puṇṇassa mantāṇiputtassa, suladdhalābhā āyasmato puṇṇassa "
"mantāṇiputtassa, "
msgstr "“Puṇṇa Mantāṇiputta is fortunate, so very fortunate, "

msgctxt "mn24:3.4"
msgid ""
"yassa viññū sabrahmacārī satthu sammukhā anumassa anumassa vaṇṇaṃ bhāsanti, "
"tañca satthā abbhanumodati."
msgstr ""
"in that his sensible spiritual companions praise him point by point in the "
"presence of the Teacher, and that the Teacher seconds that appreciation."

msgctxt "mn24:3.5"
msgid ""
"Appeva nāma mayampi kadāci karahaci āyasmatā puṇṇena mantāṇiputtena saddhiṃ "
"samāgaccheyyāma, appeva nāma siyā kocideva kathāsallāpo”ti."
msgstr ""
"Hopefully, some time or other I’ll get to meet Venerable Puṇṇa, and we can "
"have a discussion.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya4"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "mn24:4.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhagavā rājagahe yathābhirantaṃ viharitvā yena sāvatthi tena "
"cārikaṃ pakkāmi."
msgstr ""
"When the Buddha had stayed in Rājagaha as long as he wished, he set out for "
"Sāvatthī."

msgctxt "mn24:4.2"
msgid "Anupubbena cārikaṃ caramāno yena sāvatthi tadavasari."
msgstr "Traveling stage by stage, he arrived at Sāvatthī,"

msgctxt "mn24:4.3"
msgid ""
"Tatra sudaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme."
msgstr "where he stayed in Jeta’s Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery."

msgctxt "mn24:4.4"
msgid ""
"Assosi kho āyasmā puṇṇo mantāṇiputto: “bhagavā kira sāvatthiṃ anuppatto; "
"sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme”ti."
msgstr "Puṇṇa heard that the Buddha had arrived at Sāvatthī."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya5"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "mn24:5.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho āyasmā puṇṇo mantāṇiputto senāsanaṃ saṃsāmetvā pattacīvaramādāya "
"yena sāvatthi tena cārikaṃ pakkāmi."
msgstr ""
"Then he set his lodgings in order and, taking his bowl and robe, set out for "
"Sāvatthī."

msgctxt "mn24:5.2"
msgid ""
"Anupubbena cārikaṃ caramāno yena sāvatthi jetavanaṃ anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāmo "
"yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ "
"nisīdi."
msgstr ""
"Eventually he came to Sāvatthī and Jeta’s Grove. He went up to the Buddha, "
"bowed, and sat down to one side."

msgctxt "mn24:5.3"
msgid ""
"Ekamantaṃ nisinnaṃ kho āyasmantaṃ puṇṇaṃ mantāṇiputtaṃ bhagavā dhammiyā "
"kathāya sandassesi samādapesi samuttejesi sampahaṃsesi."
msgstr ""
"The Buddha educated, encouraged, fired up, and inspired him with a Dhamma "
"talk."

msgctxt "mn24:5.4"
msgid ""
"Atha kho āyasmā puṇṇo mantāṇiputto bhagavatā dhammiyā kathāya sandassito "
"samādapito samuttejito sampahaṃsito bhagavato bhāsitaṃ abhinanditvā "
"anumoditvā uṭṭhāyāsanā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā padakkhiṇaṃ katvā yena "
"andhavanaṃ tenupasaṅkami divāvihārāya."
msgstr ""
"Then, having approved and agreed with what the Buddha said, Puṇṇa got up "
"from his seat, bowed, and respectfully circled the Buddha, keeping him on "
"his right. Then he went to the Dark Forest for the day’s meditation."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya6"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi1.147"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "mn24:6.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho aññataro bhikkhu yenāyasmā sāriputto tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā "
"āyasmantaṃ sāriputtaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"Then a certain mendicant went up to Venerable Sāriputta, and said to him:"

msgctxt "mn24:6.2"
msgid ""
"“yassa kho tvaṃ, āvuso sāriputta, puṇṇassa nāma bhikkhuno mantāṇiputtassa "
"abhiṇhaṃ kittayamāno ahosi, so bhagavatā dhammiyā kathāya sandassito "
"samādapito samuttejito sampahaṃsito bhagavato bhāsitaṃ abhinanditvā "
"anumoditvā uṭṭhāyāsanā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā padakkhiṇaṃ katvā yena "
"andhavanaṃ tena pakkanto divāvihārāyā”ti."
msgstr ""
"“Reverend Sāriputta, the mendicant named Puṇṇa, of whom you have often "
"spoken so highly, after being inspired by a talk of the Buddha’s, left for "
"the Dark Forest for the day’s meditation.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya7"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "mn24:7.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho āyasmā sāriputto taramānarūpo nisīdanaṃ ādāya āyasmantaṃ puṇṇaṃ "
"mantāṇiputtaṃ piṭṭhito piṭṭhito anubandhi sīsānulokī."
msgstr ""
"Sāriputta quickly grabbed his sitting cloth and followed behind Puṇṇa, "
"keeping sight of his head."

msgctxt "mn24:7.2"
msgid ""
"Atha kho āyasmā puṇṇo mantāṇiputto andhavanaṃ ajjhogāhetvā aññatarasmiṃ "
"rukkhamūle divāvihāraṃ nisīdi."
msgstr ""
"Puṇṇa plunged deep into the Dark Forest and sat at the root of a tree for "
"the day’s meditation."

msgctxt "mn24:7.3"
msgid ""
"Āyasmāpi kho sāriputto andhavanaṃ ajjhogāhetvā aññatarasmiṃ rukkhamūle "
"divāvihāraṃ nisīdi."
msgstr "And Sāriputta did likewise."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya8"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "mn24:8.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho āyasmā sāriputto sāyanhasamayaṃ paṭisallānā vuṭṭhito yenāyasmā "
"puṇṇo mantāṇiputto tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmatā puṇṇena "
"mantāṇiputtena saddhiṃ sammodi."
msgstr ""
"Then in the late afternoon, Sāriputta came out of retreat, went to Puṇṇa, "
"and exchanged greetings with him."

msgctxt "mn24:8.2"
msgid ""
"Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ "
"nisinno kho āyasmā sāriputto āyasmantaṃ puṇṇaṃ mantāṇiputtaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"When the greetings and polite conversation were over, he sat down to one "
"side and said to Puṇṇa:"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya9"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc9"></a>
msgctxt "mn24:9.1"
msgid "“Bhagavati no, āvuso, brahmacariyaṃ vussatī”ti?"
msgstr "“Reverend, is our spiritual life lived under the Buddha?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc10"></a>
msgctxt "mn24:9.2"
msgid "“Evamāvuso”ti."
msgstr "“Yes, reverend.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc11"></a>
msgctxt "mn24:9.3"
msgid ""
"“Kiṃ nu kho, āvuso, sīlavisuddhatthaṃ bhagavati brahmacariyaṃ vussatī”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“Is the spiritual life lived under the Buddha for the sake of purification "
"of ethics?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc12"></a>
msgctxt "mn24:9.4"
msgid "“No hidaṃ, āvuso”."
msgstr "“Certainly not.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc13"></a>
msgctxt "mn24:9.5"
msgid "“Kiṃ panāvuso, cittavisuddhatthaṃ bhagavati brahmacariyaṃ vussatī”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“Then is the spiritual life lived under the Buddha for the sake of "
"purification of mind?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc14"></a>
msgctxt "mn24:9.6"
msgid "“No hidaṃ, āvuso”."
msgstr "“Certainly not.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc15"></a>
msgctxt "mn24:9.7"
msgid ""
"“Kiṃ nu kho, āvuso, diṭṭhivisuddhatthaṃ bhagavati brahmacariyaṃ vussatī”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“Is the spiritual life lived under the Buddha for the sake of purification "
"of view?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc16"></a>
msgctxt "mn24:9.8"
msgid "“No hidaṃ, āvuso”."
msgstr "“Certainly not.”"

# Cf vitareyya ogham, the basic metaphor is to move over or across, not to defeat.
#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc17"></a>
msgctxt "mn24:9.9"
msgid ""
"“Kiṃ panāvuso, kaṅkhāvitaraṇavisuddhatthaṃ bhagavati brahmacariyaṃ "
"vussatī”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“Then is the spiritual life lived under the Buddha for the sake of going "
"beyond doubt?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc18"></a>
msgctxt "mn24:9.10"
msgid "“No hidaṃ, āvuso”."
msgstr "“Certainly not.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc19"></a>
msgctxt "mn24:9.11"
msgid ""
"“Kiṃ nu kho, āvuso, maggāmaggañāṇadassanavisuddhatthaṃ bhagavati "
"brahmacariyaṃ vussatī”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“Is the spiritual life lived under the Buddha for the sake of purification "
"of knowledge and vision of the variety of paths?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc20"></a>
msgctxt "mn24:9.12"
msgid "“No hidaṃ, āvuso”."
msgstr "“Certainly not.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc21"></a>
msgctxt "mn24:9.13"
msgid ""
"“Kiṃ panāvuso, paṭipadāñāṇadassanavisuddhatthaṃ bhagavati brahmacariyaṃ "
"vussatī”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“Then is the spiritual life lived under the Buddha for the sake of "
"purification of knowledge and vision of the practice?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc22"></a>
msgctxt "mn24:9.14"
msgid "“No hidaṃ, āvuso”."
msgstr "“Certainly not.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc23"></a>
msgctxt "mn24:9.15"
msgid ""
"“Kiṃ nu kho, āvuso, ñāṇadassanavisuddhatthaṃ bhagavati brahmacariyaṃ "
"vussatī”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“Is the spiritual life lived under the Buddha for the sake of purification "
"of knowledge and vision?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc24"></a>
msgctxt "mn24:9.16"
msgid "“No hidaṃ, āvuso”."
msgstr "“Certainly not.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya10"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi1.148"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc25"></a>
msgctxt "mn24:10.1"
msgid ""
"“‘Kiṃ nu kho, āvuso, sīlavisuddhatthaṃ bhagavati brahmacariyaṃ vussatī’ti "
"iti puṭṭho samāno ‘no hidaṃ, āvuso’ti vadesi."
msgstr "“When asked each of these questions, you answered, ‘Certainly not.’"

msgctxt "mn24:10.2"
msgid ""
"‘Kiṃ panāvuso, cittavisuddhatthaṃ bhagavati brahmacariyaṃ vussatī’ti iti "
"puṭṭho samāno ‘no hidaṃ, āvuso’ti vadesi."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn24:10.3"
msgid "‘Kiṃ nu kho, āvuso, diṭṭhivisuddhatthaṃ … pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn24:10.4"
msgid "kaṅkhāvitaraṇavisuddhatthaṃ … pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn24:10.5"
msgid "maggāmaggañāṇadassanavisuddhatthaṃ … pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn24:10.6"
msgid "paṭipadāñāṇadassanavisuddhatthaṃ … pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn24:10.7"
msgid ""
"kiṃ nu kho, āvuso, ñāṇadassanavisuddhatthaṃ bhagavati brahmacariyaṃ vussatī’"
"ti iti puṭṭho samāno ‘no hidaṃ āvuso’ti vadesi."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn24:10.8"
msgid "Kimatthaṃ carahāvuso, bhagavati brahmacariyaṃ vussatī”ti?"
msgstr ""
"Then what exactly is the purpose of living the spiritual life under the "
"Buddha?”"

msgctxt "mn24:10.9"
msgid ""
"“Anupādāparinibbānatthaṃ kho, āvuso, bhagavati brahmacariyaṃ vussatī”ti."
msgstr ""
"“The purpose of living the spiritual life under the Buddha is extinguishment "
"by not grasping.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya11"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc26"></a>
msgctxt "mn24:11.1"
msgid "“Kiṃ nu kho, āvuso, sīlavisuddhi anupādāparinibbānan”ti?"
msgstr "“Reverend, is purification of ethics extinguishment by not grasping?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc27"></a>
msgctxt "mn24:11.2"
msgid "“No hidaṃ, āvuso”."
msgstr "“Certainly not.” …"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc28"></a>
msgctxt "mn24:11.3"
msgid "“Kiṃ panāvuso, cittavisuddhi anupādāparinibbānan”ti?"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc29"></a>
msgctxt "mn24:11.4"
msgid "“No hidaṃ, āvuso”."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc30"></a>
msgctxt "mn24:11.5"
msgid "“Kiṃ nu kho, āvuso, diṭṭhivisuddhi anupādāparinibbānan”ti?"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc31"></a>
msgctxt "mn24:11.6"
msgid "“No hidaṃ, āvuso”."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc32"></a>
msgctxt "mn24:11.7"
msgid "“Kiṃ panāvuso, kaṅkhāvitaraṇavisuddhi anupādāparinibbānan”ti?"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc33"></a>
msgctxt "mn24:11.8"
msgid "“No hidaṃ, āvuso”."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc34"></a>
msgctxt "mn24:11.9"
msgid ""
"“Kiṃ nu kho, āvuso, maggāmaggañāṇadassanavisuddhi anupādāparinibbānan”ti?"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc35"></a>
msgctxt "mn24:11.10"
msgid "“No hidaṃ, āvuso”."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc36"></a>
msgctxt "mn24:11.11"
msgid "“Kiṃ panāvuso, paṭipadāñāṇadassanavisuddhi anupādāparinibbānan”ti?"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc37"></a>
msgctxt "mn24:11.12"
msgid "“No hidaṃ, āvuso”."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc38"></a>
msgctxt "mn24:11.13"
msgid "“Kiṃ nu kho, āvuso, ñāṇadassanavisuddhi anupādāparinibbānan”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“Is purification of knowledge and vision extinguishment by not grasping?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc39"></a>
msgctxt "mn24:11.14"
msgid "“No hidaṃ, āvuso”."
msgstr "“Certainly not.”"

# BB has “to be attained without these states”, but this seems to be unwarranted. I am not sure if this is just an amplification, or whether it reads the -ehi as causal. However aññatra usually takes the ablative and that is the case here. Thanissaro gets this right.
#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc40"></a>
msgctxt "mn24:11.15"
msgid "“Kiṃ panāvuso, aññatra imehi dhammehi anupādāparinibbānan”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“Then is extinguishment by not grasping something apart from these things?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc41"></a>
msgctxt "mn24:11.16"
msgid "“No hidaṃ, āvuso”."
msgstr "“Certainly not.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya12"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc42"></a>
msgctxt "mn24:12.1"
msgid ""
"“‘Kiṃ nu kho, āvuso, sīlavisuddhi anupādāparinibbānan’ti iti puṭṭho samāno ‘"
"no hidaṃ, āvuso’ti vadesi."
msgstr "“When asked each of these questions, you answered, ‘Certainly not.’"

msgctxt "mn24:12.2"
msgid ""
"‘Kiṃ panāvuso, cittavisuddhi anupādāparinibbānan’ti iti puṭṭho samāno ‘no "
"hidaṃ, āvuso’ti vadesi."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn24:12.3"
msgid "‘Kiṃ nu kho, āvuso, diṭṭhivisuddhi anupādāparinibbānan’ti … pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn24:12.4"
msgid "kaṅkhāvitaraṇavisuddhi …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn24:12.5"
msgid "maggāmaggañāṇadassanavisuddhi …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn24:12.6"
msgid "paṭipadāñāṇadassanavisuddhi …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn24:12.7"
msgid ""
"‘kiṃ nu kho, āvuso, ñāṇadassanavisuddhi anupādāparinibbānan’ti iti puṭṭho "
"samāno ‘no hidaṃ, āvuso’ti vadesi."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn24:12.8"
msgid ""
"‘Kiṃ panāvuso, aññatra imehi dhammehi anupādāparinibbānan’ti iti puṭṭho "
"samāno ‘no hidaṃ, āvuso’ti vadesi."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn24:12.9"
msgid "Yathākathaṃ panāvuso, imassa bhāsitassa attho daṭṭhabbo”ti?"
msgstr "How then should we see the meaning of this statement?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya13"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc43"></a>
#. VAR: paññapeyya → paññāpessa (bj, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "mn24:13.1"
msgid ""
"“Sīlavisuddhiñce, āvuso, bhagavā anupādāparinibbānaṃ paññapeyya, "
"saupādānaṃyeva samānaṃ anupādāparinibbānaṃ paññapeyya."
msgstr ""
"“If the Buddha had declared purification of ethics to be extinguishment by "
"not grasping, he would have declared that which has grasping to be "
"extinguishment by not grasping. …"

msgctxt "mn24:13.2"
msgid ""
"Cittavisuddhiñce, āvuso, bhagavā anupādāparinibbānaṃ paññapeyya, "
"saupādānaṃyeva samānaṃ anupādāparinibbānaṃ paññapeyya."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn24:13.3"
msgid ""
"Diṭṭhivisuddhiñce, āvuso, bhagavā anupādāparinibbānaṃ paññapeyya, "
"saupādānaṃyeva samānaṃ anupādāparinibbānaṃ paññapeyya."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn24:13.4"
msgid ""
"Kaṅkhāvitaraṇavisuddhiñce, āvuso, bhagavā anupādāparinibbānaṃ paññapeyya, "
"saupādānaṃyeva samānaṃ anupādāparinibbānaṃ paññapeyya."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn24:13.5"
msgid ""
"Maggāmaggañāṇadassanavisuddhiñce, āvuso, bhagavā anupādāparinibbānaṃ "
"paññapeyya, saupādānaṃyeva samānaṃ anupādāparinibbānaṃ paññapeyya."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn24:13.6"
msgid ""
"Paṭipadāñāṇadassanavisuddhiñce, āvuso, bhagavā anupādāparinibbānaṃ "
"paññapeyya, saupādānaṃyeva samānaṃ anupādāparinibbānaṃ paññapeyya."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn24:13.7"
msgid ""
"Ñāṇadassanavisuddhiñce, āvuso, bhagavā anupādāparinibbānaṃ paññapeyya, "
"saupādānaṃyeva samānaṃ anupādāparinibbānaṃ paññapeyya."
msgstr ""
"If the Buddha had declared purification of knowledge and vision to be "
"extinguishment by not grasping, he would have declared that which has "
"grasping to be extinguishment by not grasping."

msgctxt "mn24:13.8"
msgid ""
"Aññatra ce, āvuso, imehi dhammehi anupādāparinibbānaṃ abhavissa, puthujjano "
"parinibbāyeyya."
msgstr ""
"But if extinguishment by not grasping was something apart from these things, "
"an ordinary person would become extinguished."

msgctxt "mn24:13.9"
msgid "Puthujjano hi, āvuso, aññatra imehi dhammehi."
msgstr "For an ordinary person lacks these things."

#. <a class="nya" id="nya14"></a>
msgctxt "mn24:14.1"
msgid "Tena hāvuso, upamaṃ te karissāmi;"
msgstr "Well then, reverend, I shall give you a simile."

msgctxt "mn24:14.2"
msgid "upamāyapidhekacce viññū purisā bhāsitassa atthaṃ ājānanti."
msgstr ""
"For by means of a simile some sensible people understand the meaning of what "
"is said."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi1.149"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc44"></a>
msgctxt "mn24:14.3"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, āvuso, rañño pasenadissa kosalassa sāvatthiyaṃ paṭivasantassa "
"sākete kiñcideva accāyikaṃ karaṇīyaṃ uppajjeyya."
msgstr ""
"Suppose that, while staying in Sāvatthī, King Pasenadi of Kosala had some "
"urgent business come up in Sāketa."

# https://discourse.suttacentral.net/t/on-relay-chariots-and-relays-of-chariots-and-trained-chariots/3894
msgctxt "mn24:14.4"
msgid ""
"Tassa antarā ca sāvatthiṃ antarā ca sāketaṃ satta rathavinītāni "
"upaṭṭhapeyyuṃ."
msgstr ""
"Now, between Sāvatthī and Sāketa seven prepared chariots were stationed "
"ready for him."

msgctxt "mn24:14.5"
msgid ""
"Atha kho, āvuso, rājā pasenadi kosalo sāvatthiyā nikkhamitvā antepuradvārā "
"paṭhamaṃ rathavinītaṃ abhiruheyya, paṭhamena rathavinītena dutiyaṃ "
"rathavinītaṃ pāpuṇeyya, paṭhamaṃ rathavinītaṃ vissajjeyya dutiyaṃ "
"rathavinītaṃ abhiruheyya."
msgstr ""
"Then Pasenadi, having departed Sāvatthī, mounted the first prepared chariot "
"by the gate of the royal compound. The first prepared chariot would bring "
"him to the second, where he’d dismount and mount the second chariot."

msgctxt "mn24:14.6"
msgid ""
"Dutiyena rathavinītena tatiyaṃ rathavinītaṃ pāpuṇeyya, dutiyaṃ rathavinītaṃ "
"vissajjeyya, tatiyaṃ rathavinītaṃ abhiruheyya."
msgstr "The second prepared chariot would bring him to the third …"

msgctxt "mn24:14.7"
msgid ""
"Tatiyena rathavinītena catutthaṃ rathavinītaṃ pāpuṇeyya, tatiyaṃ "
"rathavinītaṃ vissajjeyya, catutthaṃ rathavinītaṃ abhiruheyya."
msgstr "The third prepared chariot would bring him to the fourth …"

msgctxt "mn24:14.8"
msgid ""
"Catutthena rathavinītena pañcamaṃ rathavinītaṃ pāpuṇeyya, catutthaṃ "
"rathavinītaṃ vissajjeyya, pañcamaṃ rathavinītaṃ abhiruheyya."
msgstr "The fourth prepared chariot would bring him to the fifth …"

msgctxt "mn24:14.9"
msgid ""
"Pañcamena rathavinītena chaṭṭhaṃ rathavinītaṃ pāpuṇeyya, pañcamaṃ "
"rathavinītaṃ vissajjeyya, chaṭṭhaṃ rathavinītaṃ abhiruheyya."
msgstr "The fifth prepared chariot would bring him to the sixth …"

msgctxt "mn24:14.10"
msgid ""
"Chaṭṭhena rathavinītena sattamaṃ rathavinītaṃ pāpuṇeyya, chaṭṭhaṃ "
"rathavinītaṃ vissajjeyya, sattamaṃ rathavinītaṃ abhiruheyya."
msgstr ""
"The sixth prepared chariot would bring him to the seventh, where he’d "
"dismount and mount the seventh chariot."

msgctxt "mn24:14.11"
msgid "Sattamena rathavinītena sāketaṃ anupāpuṇeyya antepuradvāraṃ."
msgstr ""
"The seventh prepared chariot would bring him to the gate of the royal "
"compound of Sāketa."

msgctxt "mn24:14.12"
msgid ""
"Tamenaṃ antepuradvāragataṃ samānaṃ mittāmaccā ñātisālohitā evaṃ puccheyyuṃ:"
msgstr ""
"And when he was at the gate, friends and colleagues, relatives and kin would "
"ask him:"

msgctxt "mn24:14.13"
msgid ""
"‘iminā tvaṃ, mahārāja, rathavinītena sāvatthiyā sāketaṃ anuppatto "
"antepuradvāran’ti?"
msgstr ""
"‘Great king, did you come to Sāketa from Sāvatthī by this prepared chariot?’"

msgctxt "mn24:14.14"
msgid ""
"Kathaṃ byākaramāno nu kho, āvuso, rājā pasenadi kosalo sammā byākaramāno "
"byākareyyā”ti?"
msgstr "If asked this, how should King Pasenadi rightly reply?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc45"></a>
msgctxt "mn24:14.15"
msgid ""
"“Evaṃ byākaramāno kho, āvuso, rājā pasenadi kosalo sammā byākaramāno "
"byākareyya:"
msgstr "“The king should reply:"

#. VAR: uppajji → uppajjati (mr)
msgctxt "mn24:14.16"
msgid ""
"‘idha me sāvatthiyaṃ paṭivasantassa sākete kiñcideva accāyikaṃ karaṇīyaṃ "
"uppajji."
msgstr ""
"‘Well, while staying in Sāvatthī, I had some urgent business come up in "
"Sāketa."

msgctxt "mn24:14.17"
msgid ""
"Tassa me antarā ca sāvatthiṃ antarā ca sāketaṃ satta rathavinītāni "
"upaṭṭhapesuṃ."
msgstr ""
"Now, between Sāvatthī and Sāketa seven prepared chariots were stationed "
"ready for me."

msgctxt "mn24:14.18"
msgid ""
"Atha khvāhaṃ sāvatthiyā nikkhamitvā antepuradvārā paṭhamaṃ rathavinītaṃ "
"abhiruhiṃ."
msgstr ""
"Then, having departed Sāvatthī, I mounted the first prepared chariot by the "
"gate of the royal compound."

msgctxt "mn24:14.19"
msgid ""
"Paṭhamena rathavinītena dutiyaṃ rathavinītaṃ pāpuṇiṃ, paṭhamaṃ rathavinītaṃ "
"vissajjiṃ dutiyaṃ rathavinītaṃ abhiruhiṃ."
msgstr ""
"The first prepared chariot brought me to the second, where I dismounted and "
"mounted the second chariot. …"

msgctxt "mn24:14.20"
msgid ""
"Dutiyena rathavinītena tatiyaṃ rathavinītaṃ pāpuṇiṃ, dutiyaṃ rathavinītaṃ "
"vissajjiṃ, tatiyaṃ rathavinītaṃ abhiruhiṃ."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn24:14.21"
msgid ""
"Tatiyena rathavinītena catutthaṃ rathavinītaṃ pāpuṇiṃ, tatiyaṃ rathavinītaṃ "
"vissajjiṃ, catutthaṃ rathavinītaṃ abhiruhiṃ."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn24:14.22"
msgid ""
"Catutthena rathavinītena pañcamaṃ rathavinītaṃ pāpuṇiṃ, catutthaṃ "
"rathavinītaṃ vissajjiṃ, pañcamaṃ rathavinītaṃ abhiruhiṃ."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn24:14.23"
msgid ""
"Pañcamena rathavinītena chaṭṭhaṃ rathavinītaṃ pāpuṇiṃ, pañcamaṃ rathavinītaṃ "
"vissajjiṃ, chaṭṭhaṃ rathavinītaṃ abhiruhiṃ."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn24:14.24"
msgid ""
"Chaṭṭhena rathavinītena sattamaṃ rathavinītaṃ pāpuṇiṃ, chaṭṭhaṃ rathavinītaṃ "
"vissajjiṃ, sattamaṃ rathavinītaṃ abhiruhiṃ."
msgstr ""
"The sixth prepared chariot brought me to the seventh, where I dismounted and "
"mounted the seventh chariot."

msgctxt "mn24:14.25"
msgid "Sattamena rathavinītena sāketaṃ anuppatto antepuradvāran’ti."
msgstr ""
"The seventh prepared chariot brought me to the gate of the royal compound of "
"Sāketa.’"

msgctxt "mn24:14.26"
msgid ""
"Evaṃ byākaramāno kho, āvuso, rājā pasenadi kosalo sammā byākaramāno "
"byākareyyā”ti."
msgstr "That’s how King Pasenadi should rightly reply.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya15"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi1.150"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc46"></a>
msgctxt "mn24:15.1"
msgid ""
"“Evameva kho, āvuso, sīlavisuddhi yāvadeva cittavisuddhatthā, cittavisuddhi "
"yāvadeva diṭṭhivisuddhatthā, diṭṭhivisuddhi yāvadeva "
"kaṅkhāvitaraṇavisuddhatthā, kaṅkhāvitaraṇavisuddhi yāvadeva "
"maggāmaggañāṇadassanavisuddhatthā, maggāmaggañāṇadassanavisuddhi yāvadeva "
"paṭipadāñāṇadassanavisuddhatthā, paṭipadāñāṇadassanavisuddhi yāvadeva "
"ñāṇadassanavisuddhatthā, ñāṇadassanavisuddhi yāvadeva anupādāparinibbānatthā."
msgstr ""
"“In the same way, reverend, purification of ethics is only for the sake of "
"purification of mind. … Purification of knowledge and vision is only for the "
"sake of extinguishment by not grasping."

msgctxt "mn24:15.2"
msgid "Anupādāparinibbānatthaṃ kho, āvuso, bhagavati brahmacariyaṃ vussatī”ti."
msgstr ""
"The spiritual life is lived under the Buddha for the sake of extinguishment "
"by not grasping.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya16"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc47"></a>
msgctxt "mn24:16.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, āyasmā sāriputto āyasmantaṃ puṇṇaṃ mantāṇiputtaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "When he said this, Sāriputta said to Puṇṇa:"

msgctxt "mn24:16.2"
msgid "“konāmo āyasmā, kathañca panāyasmantaṃ sabrahmacārī jānantī”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“What is the venerable’s name? And how are you known among your spiritual "
"companions?”"

msgctxt "mn24:16.3"
msgid "“Puṇṇoti kho me, āvuso, nāmaṃ;"
msgstr "“Reverend, my name is Puṇṇa."

msgctxt "mn24:16.4"
msgid "mantāṇiputtoti ca pana maṃ sabrahmacārī jānantī”ti."
msgstr "And I am known as Mantāṇiputta among my spiritual companions.”"

msgctxt "mn24:16.5"
msgid "“Acchariyaṃ, āvuso, abbhutaṃ, āvuso."
msgstr "“It’s incredible, reverend, it’s amazing!"

msgctxt "mn24:16.6"
msgid ""
"Yathā taṃ sutavatā sāvakena sammadeva satthusāsanaṃ ājānantena, evameva "
"āyasmatā puṇṇena mantāṇiputtena gambhīrā gambhīrapañhā anumassa anumassa "
"byākatā."
msgstr ""
"Venerable Puṇṇa Mantāṇiputta has answered each deep question point by point, "
"as a learned disciple who rightly understands the teacher’s instructions."

msgctxt "mn24:16.7"
msgid "Lābhā sabrahmacārīnaṃ, suladdhalābhā sabrahmacārīnaṃ, "
msgstr "It is fortunate for his spiritual companions, so very fortunate, "

msgctxt "mn24:16.8"
msgid ""
"ye āyasmantaṃ puṇṇaṃ mantāṇiputtaṃ labhanti dassanāya, labhanti "
"payirūpāsanāya."
msgstr ""
"that they get to see Venerable Puṇṇa Mantāṇiputta and pay homage to him."

#. VAR: Celaṇḍukena → velaṇḍukena (s1-3) | celaṇḍakena (mr) | celaṇḍupekena (?)
msgctxt "mn24:16.9"
msgid ""
"Celaṇḍukena cepi sabrahmacārī āyasmantaṃ puṇṇaṃ mantāṇiputtaṃ muddhanā "
"pariharantā labheyyuṃ dassanāya, labheyyuṃ payirūpāsanāya, tesampi lābhā "
"tesampi suladdhaṃ, amhākampi lābhā amhākampi suladdhaṃ, ye mayaṃ āyasmantaṃ "
"puṇṇaṃ mantāṇiputtaṃ labhāma dassanāya, labhāma payirūpāsanāyā”ti."
msgstr ""
"Even if they only got to see him and pay respects to him by carrying him "
"around on their heads on a roll of cloth, it would still be very fortunate "
"for them! And it’s fortunate for me, so very fortunate, that I get to see "
"the venerable and pay homage to him.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya17"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi1.151"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc48"></a>
msgctxt "mn24:17.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, āyasmā puṇṇo mantāṇiputto āyasmantaṃ sāriputtaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "When he said this, Puṇṇa said to Sāriputta:"

msgctxt "mn24:17.2"
msgid "“ko nāmo āyasmā, kathañca panāyasmantaṃ sabrahmacārī jānantī”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“What is the venerable’s name? And how are you known among your spiritual "
"companions?”"

msgctxt "mn24:17.3"
msgid "“Upatissoti kho me, āvuso, nāmaṃ;"
msgstr "“Reverend, my name is Upatissa."

msgctxt "mn24:17.4"
msgid "sāriputtoti ca pana maṃ sabrahmacārī jānantī”ti."
msgstr "And I am known as Sāriputta among my spiritual companions.”"

#. VAR: bho → kho (mr)
msgctxt "mn24:17.5"
msgid "“Satthukappena vata kira, bho, sāvakena saddhiṃ mantayamānā na jānimha:"
msgstr ""
"“Goodness! I had no idea I was consulting with <em>the</em> Venerable "
"Sāriputta, the disciple who is fit to be compared with the Teacher himself!"

msgctxt "mn24:17.6"
msgid "‘āyasmā sāriputto’ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn24:17.7"
msgid ""
"Sace hi mayaṃ jāneyyāma ‘āyasmā sāriputto’ti, ettakampi no nappaṭibhāseyya."
msgstr "If I’d known, I wouldn’t have said so much."

msgctxt "mn24:17.8"
msgid "Acchariyaṃ, āvuso, abbhutaṃ, āvuso."
msgstr "It’s incredible, reverend, it’s amazing!"

msgctxt "mn24:17.9"
msgid ""
"Yathā taṃ sutavatā sāvakena sammadeva satthusāsanaṃ ājānantena, evameva "
"āyasmatā sāriputtena gambhīrā gambhīrapañhā anumassa anumassa pucchitā."
msgstr ""
"Venerable Sāriputta has asked each deep question point by point, as a "
"learned disciple who rightly understands the teacher’s instructions."

msgctxt "mn24:17.10"
msgid "Lābhā sabrahmacārīnaṃ suladdhalābhā sabrahmacārīnaṃ, "
msgstr "It is fortunate for his spiritual companions, so very fortunate, "

msgctxt "mn24:17.11"
msgid "ye āyasmantaṃ sāriputtaṃ labhanti dassanāya, labhanti payirūpāsanāya."
msgstr "that they get to see Venerable Sāriputta and pay homage to him."

msgctxt "mn24:17.12"
msgid ""
"Celaṇḍukena cepi sabrahmacārī āyasmantaṃ sāriputtaṃ muddhanā pariharantā "
"labheyyuṃ dassanāya, labheyyuṃ payirūpāsanāya, tesampi lābhā tesampi "
"suladdhaṃ, amhākampi lābhā amhākampi suladdhaṃ, ye mayaṃ āyasmantaṃ "
"sāriputtaṃ labhāma dassanāya, labhāma payirūpāsanāyā”ti."
msgstr ""
"Even if they only got to see him and pay respects to him by carrying him "
"around on their heads on a roll of cloth, it would still be very fortunate "
"for them! And it’s fortunate for me, so very fortunate, that I get to see "
"the venerable and pay homage to him.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc49"></a>
msgctxt "mn24:17.13"
msgid "Itiha te ubhopi mahānāgā aññamaññassa subhāsitaṃ samanumodiṃsūti."
msgstr "And so these two spiritual giants agreed with each others’ fine words."

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "mn24:17.14"
msgid "Rathavinītasuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ catutthaṃ."
msgstr ""
